text: Nepeta teydea is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae, native to the Canary Islands. It was first described by Philip Barker-Webb and Sabin Berthelot. Nepeta teydea kz2.JPG|Foliage Nepeta teydea Tenerife 2.jpg|Flowers ==References== teydea Category:Flora of the Canary Islands
